defaultIt is easy to claim that as everything or not enough is not known about the outcome of a new process the precautionary principle should be adopted. Discussion of the principle is more likely to be at a theoretical level rather than evidence based at the scientific level. 
defaultIs the precautionary principle adopted as a delaying tactic by people who ostensibly appear to be protecting the population from fears that they have created?
